HEALTH AND SAFETY - Aid Jokerst, Chairman (Cruts, Wisbrock, Clauss)
• Consideration of amendments to Chapter 215, Nuisances, of the City's Municipal Code. Last month, the Board approved amendments to Chapter 215, Nuisances, of the Municipal Code via Ordinance 4364. After approval, it was noted that many of the amendments were not contained in the adopted version.

Based on the above, Ordinance 4364 will need to be repealed and a new Ordinance containing all amendments will need to be approved at the September Board of Aldermen Meeting.

A copy of the proposed Chapter indicating all remaining changes not included in Ordinance 4364 was available for review.

Alderman Clauss made a motion to forward to the September Board of Aldermen meeting the amendments to Chapter 215, Nuisances, of the City's Municipal Code. The motion was seconded by Alderman Cruts. Upon a voice vote being taken, the motion passed unanimously by the Committee.

• Discussion regarding the Energy Audit Reimbursement Program offered through the Missouri Department of Natural Resources. Recently Staff received a letter from the Missouri Department of Natural Resources (MoDNR) regarding a grant opportunity for up to $20,000 towards a Level II ASHRAE energy audit to identify energy-saving updates.

Although the City had an Investment Grade Audit (IGA) in 2019 by Trane, another energy audit may be an opportunity to identify additional items that need to be addressed in all City buildings, such as the building envelope at RiverChase and the overall boiler system at City Hall - which were not fully addressed with the Trane improvements.

A copy of additional information regarding the Energy Audit Reimbursement Program that is offered through MoDNR for discussion and consideration was available for review.

Alderman Jokerst inquired if this would evaluate Trane improvements. Alderman Wisbrock suggested to compare to 2019 when facilities were in full use, not closed due to Covid, for better evaluation. City Administrator Andrea N. Finkbiner suggested using 2018 audit.

Alderman Clauss made a motion to forward to the September Board of Aldermen meeting the Energy Audit Reimbursement Program offered through the Missouri Department of Natural Resources. The motion was seconded by Alderman Clauss. Upon a voice vote being taken, the motion passed unanimously by the Committee.

